[1] South Africa: cases exceed 100 000
Date: Tue 23 Jun 2020 17:29 SAST
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-06/23/c_139161319.htm


The cumulative number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has exceeded the 100 000 mark to reach 101 590, according to the latest official update released early Tuesday [23 Jun 2020].

Another 61 deaths related to COVID-19 were added to the national death toll which now stood at 1991, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said.

The mortality rate was 2 percent while the number of recoveries stood at 53 444, translating to a recovery rate of 52.6 percent, said Mkhize.

It took South Africa 14 days to double the number of confirmed cases from 50 000 to 101 590, compared with 94 days during which the number of cases doubled and rose to 50 000 from [5 Mar to 8 Jun 2020]

The doubling of coronavirus cases in 14 days was seen as a result of the rise in mass community testing.

The country has completed 1 353 176 tests so far, of which 25 116 new tests were conducted in the past 24 hours, according to Mkhize.

